# CODEOWNERS — Require code owner review for sensitive files.
#
# When "require code owner review" is enabled on a branch protection rule,
# changes to these paths require approval from the listed owners before merge.
#
# For a personal repo this is primarily a safeguard against accidental merges
# of settings changes. In a team context it prevents privilege escalation
# via settings.yml or workflow modifications.
#
# See: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# Repository settings (branch protection, merge rules, labels)
.github/settings.yml @coreyjonoliver

# CI/CD workflows (could be used to exfiltrate secrets or skip checks)
.github/workflows/ @coreyjonoliver

# Composite actions (shared CI setup — changes affect all workflows)
.github/actions/ @coreyjonoliver

# Chezmoi config (controls what gets deployed to machines)
home/.chezmoi.toml.tmpl @coreyjonoliver

# Renovate config (controls automated dependency updates)
renovate.yaml @coreyjonoliver
